    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Containers, usually made of animal hide, made by Native North Americans to store tobacco. Often decorated with quillwork, beadwork, and sometimes pigment. Designs typically refer to cosmological or spiritual themes, as tobacco is a central aspect of many Native religious traditions.</Note_Text>
